<concept id="laylockfadectl" xml:lang="de-de">
   <title id="title__Toc50995285">LAYLOCKFADECTL System Variable</title>
   <conbody>
      <section><title>Locked layer fade control</title><p>Specifies the fading level for entities on locked layers to contrast them with entities on unlocked layers and reduces the visual complexity of a drawing. Entities on locked layers are still visible for reference and for object snapping. Non-positive values disable fading.</p><p><table id="table_r32_ncz_hnb">
               <tgroup cols="2">
                  <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*" />
                  <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="3*" />
                  <tbody>
                     <row>
                        <entry conkeyref="system_variable_warehouse/type" />
                        <entry><p conkeyref="system_variable_warehouse/short" /></entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry conkeyref="system_variable_warehouse/saved_in" />
                        <entry><p conkeyref="system_variable_warehouse/registry" /></entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry conkeyref="system_variable_warehouse/range" />
                        <entry>
                           <p>-90 to 90</p>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry conkeyref="system_variable_warehouse/default_value" />
                        <entry>
                           <p>50</p>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                  </tbody>
               </tgroup>
            </table></p></section>
   </conbody>
